  "text": "Tiainen, J. Hyvärinen, R. Sormunen, I. Miinalainen, R. Soininen, K. I. K., J. M., and P. K., unpublished data, July 2012). All these enzymes are 2-oxoglutarate dioxygenases, which require Fe 2+ , 2-oxoglutarate, O 2 and ascorbate. [CITATION_1] Hif-p4h-2 null mice die during embryonic development, whereas Hif-p4h-1 and Hif-p4h-3 null mice are viable. [CITATION_2] Broad-spectrum conditional inactivation of Hif-p4h-2 causes increased Epo production in the kidney, but not in the liver, and severe erythrocytosis, [CITATION_3] [CITATION_4] [CITATION_5] ",
